  "prompt": "What oozes out of a bug bite?",
  "response": "When you scratch or irritate a bug bite, a clear fluid called lymph may ooze out. This fluid is part of your body's immune response to the bite. In some cases, if the bite gets infected, you might also see pus, which is a thicker, often yellowish or greenish fluid that contains dead white blood cells and bacteria. It's important to keep the area clean and avoid scratching to prevent infection and further irritation.",
